# Create Product Architecture Spec (Project Overlay)

The full skill — wave-scoped technical design, capability ownership, contracts, third-party integration, configuration, failure behavior, skill-boundary delegation — is in the `praxis` plugin's `create-product-architecture-spec` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Lives at: `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/product-architecture.md`
- ADR directory: `{{paths.adr}}/`
- Engineering handbook to consult for stack invariants: `{{paths.engineering}}/handbook.md`

## Project-specific gates

- Authored or owned by the principal engineer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal-engineer}}.agent.md`) — see `.github/instructions/{{personas.aliases.principal-engineer}}-architecture.instructions.md`.
- Must explicitly call out which existing capability owns each new entity, function, or contract. New top-level capabilities require an ADR.
- Stack-specific contracts ({{stack.api_framework}} routes, {{stack.database}} schemas) must reference existing patterns. Do not invent a new shape without an ADR justifying it.

## Cross-cutting trigger

If the wave introduces a new subsystem, runtime, or trust boundary, pair this with `.github/skills/create-system-architecture/SKILL.md`.
